The paper discusses deep learning approaches for analysing digitised whole slide images from differently stained tissue sections, which is a common problem in digital pathology. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses training strategies for stain invariant networks, which involves unsupervised learning and transfer learning, indicating that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of annotations, which suggests that it may belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the analysis of multiple images, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
